Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to offer for sale this unique opportunity to acquire two significant vacant commercial lots totalling 11,766 square metres* in the heart of Robina. 

The sites have dual street frontage to Scottsdale Drive and Energy Circuit and boast uninterrupted exposure to the M1 Motorway and the railway line from Varsity Lakes to Brisbane.  The dual carriageway of Scottsdale Drive is complimented by wide street frontages, allowing the construction of significant commercial and/or logistics type operations to service the current demand for high quality assets. 

+ Lot 534 - 6,985 sqm* 
+ Lot 536 - 4,781 sqm*
+ Total land size - 11,766 sqm*
+ Zoned Special Purpose, Special Development Area

Quality infill properties like these are rarely offered to the market - this is your chance to secure your next commercial development site or build your flagship business premises.


To obtain further information, please contact the Exclusive CBRE agents listed herein. 

* Approximate

CBRE and Colliers International are pleased to present to the market for sale a development-ready site approved for multiple uses, at 299 Scottsdale Drive, Robina. 

Property features: 
- 6,763sqm* of land area
- 158m* frontage to Scottsdale Drive
- 8 storey height limit as of right**
- Maximum building coverage: 80%
- Easy & direct access to M1 Motorway, Gold Coast Airport & Brisbane Airport
- Walk to Varsity Lakes Train Station
- Sought-after Burleigh/Varsity Lakes/Robina commercial precinct
- Exceptional surrounding infrustructure and amenity 
- Zoned Special Business
- Highly exposed site, with extensive frontage to a major arterial road
- Approved for a range of commercial & other uses (suitable for developers and owner occupiers)
- Ideally suited to commercial, automotive, warehouse, showroom, medical, education and a range of other uses 

*approx
**application can be made to Council to increase the allowable height


Development in Robina enjoys major town planning benefits compared to other areas of Gold Coast city, including significant infrastructure charges savings and streamlined approval timeframes. Take advantage of this opportunity to acquire one of the last commecial sites in Robina. This property is offered to the market by way of Offers to Purchase closing Wednesday 21 April at 4pm AEST. 

For any further enquiries, please contact CBRE & Colliers exclusive agents.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: STRATEGIC COMMERCIAL & LOGISTICS SITE WITH FLEXIBLE DEVELOPMENT OPTIONS APPROVED

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Never before offered at this size
Rare approved site in central Gold Coast

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
This 2,359sqm infill site is at the heart of a high-growth amenity and infrastructure rich area.

* Adjoins established medical and retail centre

* 106-bed Japara aged care facility under construction (adjacent)

* Established public transport

* Close to Robina Town Centre, super regional shopping, dining and entertainment destination

* Close to Hospitals and Queensland Health Precinct

The site is approved for a range of uses and enjoys significant infrastructure charges savings and town planning benefits.

This is a rare opportunity to deliver a stand-alone commercial / retail / medical development or a mix of uses including residential - within a thriving, sought-after precinct.

Proposed Lot 10 has been released following the sale of approximately $17 million in development sites by master developer, Robina Group in the past year. The site at its current size has never been offered for sale, and enquiries are invited from commercial and residential developers looking for an approved development-ready site in a location with high connectivity and walkability to surrounding amenities including Robina Town Centre.

Image shown is an architectural illustration of one potential development outcome including retail at street level, plus medical and commercial office suites over four levels. Plans and yield for this indicative scheme on this boutique site are available upon request.

FOR SALE BY PRIVATE TREATY

For a detailed information memorandum including details of permitted uses, please contact appointed agents Knight Frank's Mark Witheriff or James Branch.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: RARE, APPROVED INFILL DEVELOPMENT OPPORTUNITY | BOUTIQUE MIXED-USE SITE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
20 Scottsdale Drive is a 2.628-hectare* lot that provides developers with one of the last significant land parcel offerings in Robina. 

Located in the geographical heart of the Gold Coast, in an area of rapid growth, the subject site offers an array of uses under the Robina Central Planning Agreement to assist in maximising the development's usage. The site is directly supported by substantial existing infrastructure such as Robina Town Centre, Easy-T Shopping Centre, Robina Automall, Robina Home + Life, and Bunnings. 

Direct access to the M1 Motorway, local bus services and both Robina and Varsity Lakes train stations provide the community with multiple modes of transport allowing for great access to the area.

- Potential uses include service station, fast food, convenience retail, large format and other commercial uses (STCA)  
- Surrounded by major retail developments including the Easy T Centre, Bunnings, Robina Home + Life, Robina Automall 
- Total street frontage of 431 metres*
- Zoned Special Business under the Robina Central Planning Agreement (RCPA)
- One of the last greenfield sites in CBDRobina 
- Short distance to the M1 Motorway, Robina Town Centre and Robina Train Station 
- Situated on the intersection of two major thoroughfares, Scottsdale Drive and Christine Avenue
- Robina/Varsity Lakes population 43,000* (2020 ABS ERP) 
- 12 minutes* to iconic Burleigh Heads Beach 
- 20 minutes* to Gold Coast International Airport 



*Approximate

CBRE and Colliers are pleased to offer for sale one of the last major mixed-use sites available in the Robina CBD Precinct, ideally suited to a variety of development opportunities due to the flexibility provided by the Robina Central Planning Agreement (RCPA). 

- 11,700sqm* of land with three street frontages
- High exposure corner block 
- Up to 8 storeys (as of right)
- Direct access to M1 Motorway providing swift connectivity to Gold Coast Airport, Brisbane CBD and Northern NSW 
- Adjacent to Robina Train Station and Bus Interchange 
- Short walk to Robina Town Centre, Robina Hospital, Cbus Stadium, schools, TAFE and Robina City Parklands, Gold Coast's new 22ha "Central Park" 
- Masterplan approval for up to 450 bedrooms
- Sought after residential location, with strong owner occupier and investor demand, and very low rental vacancy 
- Significant town planning benefits including substantial infrastructure charge savings 
* City skyline views are likely to be achieved from approximately Level 3 to Level 8 of a future development 


Contact the exclusive agents now to find out more about this landmark development opportunity in an amenity-rich, central location. A detailed Information Memorandum is available upon request.
